<article>
    <h1>Christ&#xAD;mas book boxes</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201213/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-13"><time>2020-12-13</time></a>
        - <span>FEATURES</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Fancy hav­ing your fes­tive reads de­liv­ered to your doorstep all wrapped up in a box?</p>
    <p>Check out some of the Christ­mas boxes cu­rated by book­sell­ers here.</p>
    <p>Book­sAc­tu­ally (book­s­ac­tu­allyshop.com)and dis­trib­u­tor Times Reads have put to­gether three lim­ited-edi­tion $88 boxes. There are 50 of each type of box, with books such as Zadie Smith’s es­say col­lec­tion In­ti­ma­tions and The Puf­fin Book Of Christ­mas Sto­ries. The Yel­low box, which is for ages 12 and be­low, con­tains an A5 sticker sheet fea­tur­ing Book­sAc­tu­ally’s res­i­dent cats Cake, Pico and Lemon.</p>
    <p>On­line chil­dren’s re­tailer Natven­ture Books (natven­ture­books.com) has cu­rated three boxes of books, toys and snacks for kids, from Love In A Box ($38.50) for those aged three and be­low, to the Bug Ex­plorer Box ($69.90) for young bug en­thu­si­asts.</p>
    <p>Times Book­stores (goguru.com.sg) is of­fer­ing Christ­mas bun­dles of books, sta­tionery and care prod­ucts. Some are for kids, while there is also a self-care bun­dle and a lit­er­ary bun­dle with books like lo­cal love story an­thol­ogy A View Of Stars.</p>


